The paper deals with data mining and optimization, which are core topics in computer science. The methodology presented in the paper is applicable to a wide range of problems, making it relevant to several sub-categories. The focus on optimization suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The use of data mining and machine learning techniques suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely. The application of the methodology to logistics and transportation problems suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are also possible sub-categories.
